-- Colombia Stocks: Helm Bank and Pacific Rubiales Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-13T20:46:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/colombia-stocks-helm-bank-and-pacific-rubiales-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in  Colombia .  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.3 percent to 15,073.02 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  dropped 0.4 percent to 1,748.70.  Helm Bank SA (PFBHELM)  (PFBHELMB CB), a Colombian lender, rose 3.7
percent to 539 pesos. The Bogota-based bank’s shares have surged
46 percent this month on speculation it will be acquired. Helm
Corp., the controlling shareholder, said April 10 that it hired
an investment bank to “advise in the analysis of business
alternatives for its investment.”  Pacific Rubiales SA (PRE)   fell 1 percent to 50,900
pesos. The Toronto-based oil producer that operates fields in
Colombia dropped in line with the price of crude.  To contact the reporter on this story:
